snippet.title: Alice in Borderland: Season 3 | Official Teaser | Netflix
snippet.description:
The survival action series "Alice in Borderland" became the most watched Japanese Netflix title by worldwide audiences.

Now, the "games" that took the world by storm begin once again.

In the previous season, Arisu (#KentoYamazaki) and Usagi (#TaoTsuchiya) cleared all of the games and returned to the real world. They have since gotten married and established a happy life together. Their memories of the borderland were erased, but they see glimpses of it in dreams and hallucinations. One day, Usagi, led by afterlife researcher Ryuji (#KentoKaku), suddenly vanishes. At the same time as Usagi's disappearance, Banda (#HayatoIsomura) hands Arisu the final card: the Joker.

The uncharted journey led by the mysterious Joker card is about to unfold...

Season 3 of the Netflix Series "Alice in Borderland" is set for worldwide release on Thursday, September 25, 2025, only on Netflix.

Watch on Netflix: https://www.netflix.com/title/81682895

About Netflix:
Netflix is one of the world's leading entertainment services, with over 300 million paid memberships in over 190 countries enjoying TV series, films and games across a wide variety of genres and languages. Members can play, pause and resume watching as much as they want, anytime, anywhere, and can change their plans at any time.

Alice in Borderland: Season 3 | Official Teaser | Netflix
https://www.youtube.com/@Netflix

As new deadly games return, Arisu, Usagi and new players must navigate even more daunting, adrenaline-fueled challenges.

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. snippet.description:

Our Truth. Our History.

Directed by Nitesh Tiwari, Produced by Namit Malhotra‚Äôs Prime Focus Studios and 8-time Oscar winning VFX studio DNEG in association with Yash‚Äôs Monster Mind Creations; Ramayana is being filmed for IMAX and will release worldwide: Part 1 on Diwali 2026 and Part 2 on Diwali 2027.

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada

snippet.description:
Step into Jethalal‚Äôs world with Gada Electronics!  Manage the shop, tackle quirky customers, and experience nonstop TMKOC-style fun. Are you ready for the challenge? 

 Play now: https://gadaelectronics.page.link/dhgB  #GadaElectronics #TMKOCGame

Click here to Subscribe to Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Official Channel: https://www.youtube.com/taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah?sub_confirmation=1 

Click here to watch NEW Episode videos: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzSxhJ6UCi6tgujD-FsAy0sw

Click here to watch your favourite videos from Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: 
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Cast:
---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada
Nitish Bhaluni / Raj Anadkat / Bhavya Gandhi as Tipendra Jethalal Gada (Tapu) 
Amit Bhatt as Champaklal Jayantilal Gada
Sachin Shroff / Shailesh Lodha as Taarak Mehta
Sunayana Fozdar / Neha Mehta as Anjali Taarak Mehta
Tanuj Mahashabde as Krishnan Subramaniam Iyer
Munmun Dutta as Babita Krishnan Iyer
Mandar Chandwadkar as Aatmaram Tukaram Bhide
Sonalika Joshi as Madhvi Aatmaram Bhide
Nidhi Bhanushali / Palak Sidhwani / Khushi Mali as Sonalika Aatmaram Bhide (Sonu) 
Gurucharan Singh/ Balwinder Suri as Roshan Singh Harjeet Singh Sodhi
Jennifer Mistry Bansiwal as Roshan Kaur Roshan Singh Sodhi
Kavi Kumar Azad / Nirmal Soni as Dr. Hansraj Hathi 
Ambika Ranjankar as Komal Hansraj Hathi
Kush Shah as Gulabkumar Hansraj Hathi (Goli)
Shyam Pathak as Popatlal Pandey
Sharad Sankla as Abdul
Azhar Shaikh as Pinku 
Ghanshyam Nayak / Kiran Bhatt as Nattu Kaka
Tanmay Vekaria as Bagha
Navina Wadekar / Monika Bhadoriya as Bawri

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

localized.title: Chhodh Ke Na Jaa Ooh Piya (Lyrical Video) | Alka Yagnik | Sunny Deol, Tabu | Maa Tujhhe Salaam
localized.description:
"Chhodh Ke Na Jaa Ooh Piya" is a soulful and emotional track from the movie Maa Tujhhe Salaam (2002), beautifully sung by Alka Yagnik. The song expresses a deep sense of love, longing, and heartache, as the singer pleads with her lover not to leave. With its heartfelt lyrics and Alka Yagnik‚Äôs powerful voice, this song stands out as one of the most poignant and memorable moments in the film.

Music: Sajid-Wajid
Lyrics: Sameer
Movie: Maa Tujhhe Salaam
Starring: Sunny Deol, Tabu
Director: Tinu Verma
Producer: Mahendra Dhariwal
Label: Universal Music India

snippet.title: Headlights - Udta Jaaye @alok (ft. @KRSNAOfficial & @RashmeetKaur ) | Free Fire MAX
snippet.description:
When DJ Alok touched down in India, we knew we had to cook up a banger üí•
With your favorites @KRSNAOfficial and @RashmeetKaur on the track...we turned the heat all the way up üî•üé∂

SONG LYRICS:

Ab to ye Udta Jaaye, dil mera Udta Jaaye,
Jo chahe woh paa jaaye, awara Udta Jaaye.
O-Ohhh junoon har saans mein,
O-Ohhh hatheli par hai jaan,
O-Ohhh tum hi rakho zameen,
O-Ohhh mera hai aasmaan.

Ab to ye Udta Jaaye, dil mera Udta Jaaye,
Jo chahe woh paa jaaye, awara Udta Jaaye.
Haan ye dil Udta Jaaye, poochho na ye kahaan jaaye,
Jo chahe woh paa jaaye, awara Udta Jaaye.
Ab to ye Udta Jaaye, dil mera Udta Jaaye,
Jo chahe woh paa jaaye, awara Udta Jaaye.
Haan ye dil Udta Jaaye, poochho na ye kahaan jaaye,
Jo chahe woh paa jaaye, awara Udta Jaaye.

Dekho aaj bhi main ladoon jaise kuchh nahi hai khone ko,
Kone kone mein jaane log, ab poochhe na kaun hai woh.
Itne sapne dekhe toh milta nahi hai sone ko,
Iss game mein top brass, ye peetal bolenge sone ko.
Bole kaam kar, maine kare kaam fir,
Hota na pareshan, meri lage jaan fir,
Subah chale shaam, chale sar-e-aam fir,
Jab kalam se chale chaal, bane kalamkaar fir.


O-Ohhh har pal hai aakhri, O-Ohhh hai kal ki kya khabar,
O-Ohhh jeena hai aaj mein, O-Ohhh haan hoon main befikr.
Ho-Ooo hai aag seene mein, Ho-Toh maza hai jeene mein,
O-Aaa har pal se zindagi, Oo-Aa jee bhar ke jee lenge.

Ab to ye Udta Jaaye, dil mera Udta Jaaye,
Jo chahe woh paa jaaye, awara Udta Jaaye.
Haan ye dil Udta Jaaye, poochho na ye kahaan jaaye,
Jo chahe woh paa jaaye, awara Udta Jaaye.

Kari hai raat kaali,
Dekhe maine bhi khwaab,
Haan mushkil dekhe maine din,
Dekhe maine bhi raat.
Iss level se na sehmati hai,
Mujhse mehnati kaun?
I got the skill to make
A kill N wipe an enemy squad.
I say ‚Äì Booyah!
Jaake la tu crew-ya,
Kaun hai tu yaar?
Coz I never knew-ya.
I‚Äôm making moves-ya,
Ikattha karoon loot-ya,
Phir bhi tu lage noob,
Coz I‚Äôm shootin through-ya.
I‚Äôm singing‚Ä¶

Jo chahe woh paa jaaye, awara Udta Jaaye.

Ab kepada kamu Udta Jaaye, dil mera Udta Jaaye,
Jo chahe woh paa jaaye, awara Udta Jaaye.

O-Ohhh junoon har saans mein,
O-Ohhh hatheli par hai jaan,
O-Ohhh tum hai rakho zameen,
O-Ohhh mera hai aasmaan.

Ab kepada kamu Udta Jaaye, dil mera Udta Jaaye,
Jo chahe woh paa jaaye, awara Udta Jaaye.

Ya, hatiku melayang, jangan tanya ke mana ia harus pergi,
Biarkan apa pun yang kuinginkan ditemukan, ia harus terbang menjauh.
Sekarang ia melayang, hatiku melayang,
Biarkan apa pun yang kuinginkan ditemukan, ia harus terbang menjauh.
Ya, hatiku melayang, jangan tanya ke mana ia harus pergi,
Biarkan apa pun yang kuinginkan ditemukan, ia harus terbang menjauh.

Lihat, bahkan hari ini aku bodoh, tak ada ruginya,

Aku tak bisa tidur bahkan setelah melihat begitu banyak mimpi,
Dalam permainan ini, akulah petinggi, orang-orang ini akan berkata emas.

Biarkan aku berjalan di pagi dan sore hari, biarkan aku berjalan sepanjang hari,
Ketika aku berjalan dengan penaku, aku akan menjadi penulis lagi.

O-Ohhh setiap saat adalah yang terakhir, O-Ohhh apa kabar tentang esok hari,
O-Ohhh aku harus hidup hari ini, O-Ohhh ya, aku riang.

Malam itu gelap,

Aku juga melihat mimpi,

Ya, aku melihat kesulitan di siang hari,

Aku juga melihat malam.

Aku tidak punya kesabaran sehebat ini,

Siapa yang lebih rajin dariku?

Aku punya kemampuan untuk membuat

Membunuh atau menyapu bersih pasukan musuh.

Kukatakan - Booyah!

Pergilah ke kru-mu,

Siapa kau, kawan?

Karena aku tak pernah tahu.

Aku bergerak,
Mari kita menjarah bersama,
Tapi kau masih terlihat seperti orang bodoh,
Karena aku terus menembak.
Aku bernyanyi...

Kini hatiku melayang, hatiku melayang,
Biarkan aku mendapatkan apa pun yang kuinginkan, biarkan aku terbang.

Ya, hatiku melayang, jangan tanya ke mana perginya,

snippet.title: ‡Æ§‡ØÅ‡Æ™‡Ææ‡ÆØ‡Øç‡Æ≤ ‡Æï‡Æ±‡Øç‡Æ™‡Æ©‡Øà ‡Æö‡ØÜ‡ÆØ‡Øç‡ÆØ ‡ÆÆ‡ØÅ‡Æü‡Æø‡ÆØ‡Ææ‡Æ§ ‡Æí‡Æ∞‡ØÅ  ‡Æ§‡ØÄ‡Æµ‡ØÅ‡Æï‡Øç‡Æï‡ØÅ ‡Æ™‡Øã‡Æ±‡Øã‡ÆÆ‡Øç | Exclusive | Dubai | Chapter 1
snippet.description:
üåç Exploring The Heart of Europe ‚Äì A European Island Hidden Inside Dubai üá¶üá™

The journey begins at Al Wasl Marine Transport Station, boarding a high-speed boat to the iconic World Islands. As the boat races across the Arabian Gulf, the story of how these islands were built unfolds ‚Äî a bold vision of recreating the world map in the sea.

The first stop is VOCO Monaco. From the very first step, it feels like stepping into Europe ‚Äî colorful streets, unique architecture, and the surprise of Rain Street, where it drizzles even under Dubai‚Äôs bright sun.

From there, a boat ride takes you across the island clusters, passing stunning recreations of European destinations like Sweden‚Äôs floating palaces, Venice-style canals, and other themed spaces that make up The Heart of Europe. Each one reflects authentic design and atmosphere from across the continent.

The next stop is the Coral Institute ‚Äî a fascinating initiative focused on marine conservation. Here, coral regeneration and marine ecosystem research are done with futuristic vision and purpose.

Then comes one of the most breathtaking highlights ‚Äî the Floating Seahorse Villa, a luxurious residence with a spacious open deck above water and a serene underwater bedroom below. Seeing this kind of engineering and comfort combined in the middle of the sea is truly a once-in-a-lifetime moment.

The experience continues at the Smart Police Station (SPS) ‚Äî a fully automated, contactless station. A brief conversation with the officer reveals how the system works and how it‚Äôs redefining city services.

Back at VOCO Monaco, a special Malaysian-style chicken satay is prepared by celebrity chef Vibin. As the sun begins to set, there‚Äôs time to connect with the team, relax by the beach, and take in the lively Budapest-style beach party before returning to the Dubai mainland.

This is not just a tour ‚Äî it‚Äôs a cinematic journey into a future-ready European world crafted inside Dubai.

Lyrics:
Pallavi:
Vela vela vennelantha
Meedha vaali velugunantha
Moyamante nenu entha.. Arere‚Ä¶
Chinni gunde unnadhentha
Haayi nimpi gaalinantha
Oodhamante oopirentha.. Arere‚Ä¶
Kallu rendu pusthakaalu
Bhasha leni aksharaalu
Choopulone ardhamayye.. Anni maatalu‚Ä¶
Mundhu leni aanavaalu
Leniponi kaaranaalu
Kotha kotha onamaalu.. Enni maayalu‚Ä¶
Kathalenno cheppaaru
Kavithalni raasaaru
Kaalaalu dhaataaru
Yuddhaalu chesaaru
Premalo.. Thappu ledhu premalo.. || 2 ||

Charanam 1:
Aakaasham thaakaali ani undha
Naatho raa chupisthaa aa saradhaa
Nelanthaa chuttese veelundhaa
Emundhi premisthe saripodhaa
Aha mabbulanni kommalai
Poolavaana pampithe
Aa vaana peru prema le
Dhaani ooru manamu le
Ye manasuni yemadagaku ye rujuvini.. Oh.. Anthe.. Oh..
|| Kathalenno ||

Charanam 2:
Enthunte entantaa dhooraalu
Rekkallaa ayipothe paadhaalu
Unnaayaa bandhinche dhaaraalu
Oohallo untunte praanaalu
Are ningi loni chukkale
Kindhakochi cherithe
Avi neeku edhuru nilipithe
Undipova ikkade
Jaabili itu cherenu porapaatuna ani.. Oh.. Inthe.. Oh..
|| Kathalenno ||
